New Records: The Angels lost their 96th game, setting a franchise record for losses.
Key Match Events: The White Sox scored 7 runs in the fifth inning, their season high.
Shortstop Zach Neto left the game with right shoulder irritation after sliding head-first into second base.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Ron Washington stated, 'It’s pretty sickening.'

Catch Logan O’Hoppe said, 'Going in the spring and expecting things to turn around, and then it happens. We’ve got a good group in here, and it doesn’t feel like what the record shows, but the record is what it is. I don’t think anyone’s OK with it here.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Left-hander Tyler Anderson had a rough outing, giving up 4 earned runs and ending his season with a 3.81 ERA in 31 starts.
Zach Neto might return to the lineup as soon as Saturday.
